  "prompt": "My mom makes me eat less than my BMR for weight loss. what should I do?",
  "response": "I'm really sorry you're going through this. Your health and well-being are incredibly important. Here are a few steps you might consider:\n\n1. **Talk to a Trusted Adult:** This could be another family member, a teacher, a school counselor, or a family friend. Sharing your feelings and concerns with someone you trust can provide support and guidance.\n\n2. **Seek Professional Help:** Consider reaching out to a healthcare professional, such as a doctor or a mental health counselor. They can offer you expert advice and help you navigate this situation safely.\n\n3. **Educate Yourself and Your Family:** Understanding the basics of nutrition and a healthy relationship with food might help in conversations with your mom. Sometimes, providing factual information can make a difference.\n\n4. **Express Your Feelings:** If you feel comfortable, try to have an open and honest conversation with your mom about how her actions are affecting you. Use \"I\" statements to express your feelings without sounding accusatory (e.g., \"I feel worried about my health when I don't eat enough\").\n\n5. **Reach Out to Support Groups:** There are organizations and support groups dedicated to helping individuals facing similar challenges. Connecting with others can provide additional support and resources.\n\nRemember, your well-being is paramount, and seeking help is a strong and positive step toward ensuring your health and happiness.",
